{'summary_detail': {'base': 'http://planet.debian.org/rss20.xml', 'type': 'text/html', 'value': u'Actually they\'re more interested in freedom, to be no longer slaves to humans. I don\'t think it\'s any spoiler to mention that an <a href="http://www.electricsheep.org/" class="zem_slink" rel="homepage" title="Electric Sheep">electric sheep</a> does appear in the book.<br /><br />This is a classic <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Science_fiction" class="zem_slink" rel="wikipedia" title="Science fiction">science fiction</a> story of a dark not-so-distant future.\xa0 In fact given that it\'s over 40 years old it could be set in some alternate now.\xa0 Some disaster has occurred and many have either left earth or died.\xa0 Some andriods, or andys have escaped and bounty hunters are after them.<br /><br />You may not know the book by its correct title, but you may of heard the movie that is based upon it, called <a href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0083658/" class="zem_slink" rel="imdb" title="Blade Runner">Blade Runner</a>.\xa0 Like most movies based on books, it takes some of the concepts and ideas of the book but in my opinion is a pale imitation.<br /><br />I\'m glad I read this book. It hasn\'t aged that much and it\'s very though provoking.\xa0 Sci-Fi often uses some alternate reality to put a mirror up to what happens in the real world and this book is no exception.<br /><br />\n\nAnd a token link to <a href="http://www.debian.org/" class="autolink">Debian</a>, if you want you own electric sheep you can install the screensaver <a href="http://packages.debian.org/sid/electricsheep">electricsheep</a> package which draw pretty <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fractal" class="zem_slink" rel="wikipedia" title="Fractal">fractals</a> on your screen.<br /><br /><fieldset class="zemanta-related"><legend class="zemanta-related-title">Related articles by Zemanta</legend><ul class="zemanta-article-ul"><li class="zemanta-article-ul-li"><a href="http://www.huffingtonpo